-Mn5w3m8s50Jizln3NWj.name: Connected Places Catapult
-Mn5w3m8s50Jizln3NWj.programmeObjectives:
Innovation as a Service
At Connected Places Catapult, we provide impartial ‘innovation as a service’ for mobility and built environment businesses, infrastructure providers and public institutions to catalyse step-change improvements in the way people live, work and travel.

Commercialising Cutting-edge Research
We connect businesses and public sector leaders to cutting-edge research. We help develop, implement and commercialise the latest technology and innovation for existing markets, as well as create demand and grow new markets in the UK and globally. In addition to the many projects we’re working on with our partners, we run technology demonstrations and innovation accelerators for SMEs to help scale new solutions that drive business growth while contributing to the economic growth and a better, greener future for all.
-Mn5w3m8s50Jizln3NWj.programmeSummary: Connected Places Catapult is the UK’s innovation accelerator for cities, transport, and places.

-Mn5zJLU3moP-LhoR-kJ.name: WeSprint Venture Builder
-Mn5zJLU3moP-LhoR-kJ.programmeObjectives:
We  host  focused workshops and sprints that connect Founders and SMEs to our ecosystems of Investors and Commercial partners.

We unpack data, talent and revenue and distill the value to:

- Prioritise activity to drives value
- Build scalable frameworks for talent internal and external 
- Cultivate and execute on clients that amplify your IP value
- Speak the language of Investors and market leaders in your sector
- Curate a community of individuals and organisations that test and prove your IP
-Mn5zJLU3moP-LhoR-kJ.programmeSummary: World Class Venture Builder for the new and established. We work with SMEs, Direct and In-direct Investors.

-Mn66GX6iReIIo69a6r0.name: UCL/Bloomsbury Startup Academy
-Mn66GX6iReIIo69a6r0.programmeObjectives:
1:1 MENTORING

You will be matched with a real entrepreneur who is working in the same or similar sector to your idea, providing you tailored advice, support and mentorship throughout the programme.
BSA GET-TOGETHERS

Meet your fellow participants in the programme a little better through our occasional meet-ups and bounce your idea off them, maybe even team up, it's up to you.
IDEA SURGERIES

Throughout the 5-week programme, you will be delivered bi-weekly workshop style sessions called 'Idea Surgeries' to refine your idea into a business plan, from the legals to financials.
LIFT OFF

The culmination of the programme, you will pitch your business plan to some of London's top entrepreneurs for a chance to win £1,000 of non-equity seed capital.
-Mn66GX6iReIIo69a6r0.programmeSummary:
The Bloomsbury Startup Academy is UCLe’s exciting new startup accelerator, expanding on the past success of the Moonshot Launchpad. In helping budding student entrepreneurs navigate the difficult early stages of their startup creation, we’ve already supported dozens of groups in their journey of innovation and enterprise – and we can’t wait to help more! 
 
With a new remit of leading an alliance comprising UCL’s premier technical societies, the BSA helps startup ideas ranging from VR surgery to window-washing drones.
